{"id":2338,"date":"2024-12-02T16:22:23","date_gmt":"2024-12-02T16:22:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/?post_type=wiki&#038;p=2338"},"modified":"2024-12-02T16:25:54","modified_gmt":"2024-12-02T16:25:54","slug":"game-settings","status":"publish","type":"wiki","link":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/game-mechanics\/game-settings\/","title":{"rendered":"Game Settings &amp; Options"},"content":{"rendered":"<table class=\"table left grey\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Setting<\/th>\n<th>What It Does<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><u>General Options<\/u><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>R-Button Mode<\/td>\n<td>Changes what the R-Button can be used for in the overworld.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>L-Button Mode<\/td>\n<td>Changes what the L-Button can be used for in the overworld (but also in other places for L=A).<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Save Prompts<\/td>\n<td>The game will ask you if you want to save at key moments.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Skip Cutscenes<\/td>\n<td>Skip certain story cutscenes.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Puzzle Difficulty<\/td>\n<td>Change the difficulty of overworld puzzles.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Auto Item Sort<\/td>\n<td>Auto sorts the Cube&#8217;s Items sector either by Name, Type or by Amount.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Quick HM<\/td>\n<td>If you interact with something that you can use an HM on, your Pokemon will use the HM and not ask you first.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Frame<\/td>\n<td>Changes the default window frame.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><u>Battle Options<\/u><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Battle Effects<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to turn off most of the animations that play in battle.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Battle Style<\/td>\n<td>Changes whether the game will ask you if you want to switch Pokemon after defeating a Trainer&#8217;s Pokemon.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Battle Difficulty<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to decrease the difficulty of Trainer battles. Harder modes are only available at the start of the game. There is no flip-flopping between Vanilla and harder modes to gain more Exp. throughout the course of the game. Difficult mode may still be accessed from Vanilla mode, however.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Item Restrictions<\/td>\n<td>Rules for using items in Trainer battles.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Exp. Gain<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to give Exp to your entire party after defeating a Pokemon. An optional level-cap also presents here.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Quick Run<\/td>\n<td>Set the button combination for fleeing quickly.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Team Preview<\/td>\n<td>Show prompt to view enemy team.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Last Used Ball<\/td>\n<td>Show prompt to use last Pok\u00e9 Ball.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fast Messages<\/td>\n<td>If enabled, the game won&#8217;t pause for a certain period of time after displaying a message in battle.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Type Icons<\/td>\n<td>Displays type icons next to the health bar in all battles, not just Camomons.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nickname Offer<\/td>\n<td>Offer to nickname a caught, given or bought Pok\u00e9mon.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Take Wild Item<\/td>\n<td>Put a caught Pok\u00e9mon&#8217;s item in the Cube.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><u>Audio Options<\/u><\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Overworld Theme<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to override the default music that plays in the overworld.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Wild Theme<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to override the default music that plays in wild battles.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Trainer Theme<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to override the default music that plays in Trainer battles.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Audio Quality<\/td>\n<td>Set the quality of all game audio.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Speakers<\/td>\n<td>Changes the default audio output to either stereo or mono.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sound Effects<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to turn off in-game sound effect.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Background Music<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to turn off background music.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bike &amp; Surf Music<\/td>\n<td>Can be used to turn off themes when biking and surfing.<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/game-mechanics\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/bedroom-unbound.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/bedroom-unbound.jpg 400w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/bedroom-unbound-200x200.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Game Mechanics<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":2339,"parent":2336,"menu_order":2,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"class_list":["post-2338","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2338","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2336"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2339"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2338"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2338"}],"curies":[{"